data.title: Haddiscoe Bridge, Haddiscoe New Cut, Haddiscoe, Norfolk
data.meta_description: A view looking south showing the old bascule bridge crossing the new cut and a train passing the original haddiscoe station on the opposite bank. A bascule bridge (sometimes referred to as a drawbridge) is a moveable bridge that opens to let boats pass through.
data.text:
A view looking south showing the old bascule bridge crossing the new cut and a train passing the original haddiscoe station on the opposite bank. A bascule bridge (sometimes referred to as a drawbridge) is a moveable bridge that opens to let boats pass through.

Location

Norfolk Haddiscoe

Period

1950s (1950 - 1959)
